FbWFpbCIsIlR5cGUiOiJOb3RpZmljYXRpb24iLCJTSUQiOiJtcy52c3MtY29kZS5wdWxsLXJlcXVlc3QtdXBkYXRlZC1zdWJzY3JpcHRpb24iLCJTVHlwZSI6IkNPTiIsIlJlY2lwIjoyLCJFbGVtZW50IjoiYnJhbmNoZXMvdGFyZ2V0QnJhbmNoTGluayJ9#version=GBdevelop\">develop</a>\n\n                </td>\n              </tr>\n\n              <tr>\n                <td class=\"message\" style=\"padding: 0 0 24px 0\">\n                    <p style=\"font-family: 'Segoe UI', '-apple-system', 'BlinkMacSystemFont', 'Roboto', 'Arial', sans-serif; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; color: #444444; word-break: break-word;\">\n\n        <ul style=\"list-style-type: disc\">\n            \n                \n                    <li>*\tSource branch delete failed</li>\n                                                                    \n            <li>*\tAutomatically completed</li>\n\n            <li>*\tBranch was merged</li>\n                            </ul>\n    <br>\n\n<h2>What</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>*\tSwitch the insights agent to report all monetary values in the customer's local currency instead of defaulting to EUR — across BI data, agent prompts, the briefing, the PDF export, and the UI.  \n</li>\n<li>*\tConsolidate the BI sales/AR queries onto two currency-aware stored procedures (SP_INVOICED_SALES, SP_OUTSTANDING_SALES), aggregating product×month sales in C#; remove the redundant inline queries, the usp_* variants, BiSalesRow/BiPaymentRow, and drop the AR table from the insights path.  \n</li>\n<li>*\tCoordinated rename of all *Eur/_eur monetary symbols to neutral names (C# models, prompt JSON, briefing JSON, PDF, front-end); each value now carries an iso_currency_code sourced from the CRM account, and the PDF/UI format via the ISO→symbol path with dual-key back-compat for persisted briefings.  \n</li>\n<li>*\tMake the sales-analyzer prompt currency-aware and render the currency symbol (€/$/£…) in textual outputs (key points, narratives, overdue-invoice actions) instead of the bare ISO code.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Notes</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>*\tExternal dependency: the BI local-currency columns (sales/gp1/cogs_localcurrency on SP_INVOICED_SALES; amount_localcurrency + invoice fields on SP_OUTSTANDING_SALES) must exist in the BI database. Columns are mapped defensively, so values read as 0 until they land.  \n</li>\n<li>*\tFixed a confirmed pre-existing bug: CustomerBriefBuilder read value_eur while the producer emits value, so high-value early-stage opportunities never reached the market-intelligence brief.  \n</li>\n<li>*\tOne currency per customer is assumed (SUM-based totals stay valid); a non-fatal log fires if the BI currency disagrees with the CRM account currency.  \n</li>\n<li>*\tCross-sell path intentionally out of scope.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Quality</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>*\tResolved: W-001 (FormatEur delegates to FormatCurrency(value, null)), W-004 (PipelineValueThresholdEur renamed).  \n</li>\n<li>*\tDeferred (non-blocking): W-002 — no debug log on null ISO code in the static PDF renderers (logger threading deferred); W-003 — BiService.cs exceeds the 200-line threshold (partial-class split deferred).  \n</li>\n<li>*\tFollow-up: the ISO→symbol map is now duplicated across client / MCP / Worker — candidate for a shared Core helper.</li>\n</ul>\n\n</p>\n               </td>\n              </tr>\n              \n\n              <tr>\n                <td style=\"padding: 0 0 24px 0\">\n                    \n\n\n\n<table width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n  <tr>\n    <td>\n      <table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n        <tr>\n              \n              <td align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#007acc\" style=\"padding: 8px 12px; border-radius: 2px;\">\n                <a href=\"https://eur02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fdev.azure.com%2FAzelis%2FAI%2520Sales%2520Agents%2F_git%2FAI%2520Sales%2520Agents%2Fpullrequest%2F3707%3Ftracking_data%%253d%253d&amp;data=demo.user%40example.com%7C9ce65990ef4548b920b408dec